== D.9 — Glossary of Key Terms

#table(
  columns: (auto, 1fr),
  stroke: 0.5pt + ttao-rule,
  fill: (col, row) => if row == 0 { ttao-mid } else if calc.odd(row) { ttao-pale } else { white },
  inset: 0.5em,
  text(fill: white, weight: "bold")[Term],
  text(fill: white, weight: "bold")[Definition],

  [*Archaeus*],          [The inner master-spirit or vital force governing the body's alchemical processes from within. The inner alchemist; the executive intelligence of the organism.],
  [*Caput Mortuum*],     ["Dead head" — the residual feces after the macerate has been poured off. Not discarded; calcined to recover the Salt.],
  [*Cohobation*],        [The pouring of the volatile fraction back over the fixed salt. Each repetition increases potency by elevating the reunion.],
  [*Gur*],               [The concentrated seed-matter that forms during long putrefaction of water. The alchemical equivalent of the plant Salt in the water kingdom.],
  [*Ingress*],           [The capacity of the calcined Salt to absorb the essence during cohobation. Lost through vitrification. Essential for the preparation to proceed.],
  [*Maceration*],        [Extraction by soaking in a menstruum (usually rectified spirit of wine) over days or weeks at gentle warmth.],
  [*Menstruum*],         [The solvent used for extraction. In Year One, rectified spirits of wine. Must pass the Cotton Wick Test.],
  [*Nigredo*],           [The Black Stage — the first and most demanding colour stage. Putrefaction, dissolution, the apparent chaos that precedes regeneration.],
  [*Peacock's Tail*],    [Cauda Pavonis — the iridescent display of many colours that appears in a sealed preparation between the Nigredo and Albedo. A reliable sign of correct progress.],
  [*Philosophic Mercury*],[Not common quicksilver. The universal volatile principle prepared and concentrated for use as a solvent or vehicle. In each kingdom it takes a specific form.],
  [*Prima Materia*],     [The first matter — the undifferentiated source from which all things are derived and to which all things return through putrefaction.],
  [*Rectification*],     [The repeated distillation of a fraction to increase its purity and concentration. Removes residual Mercury or Sulphur from the heart fraction.],
  [*Rubedo*],            [The Red Stage — the final colour stage. The Stone fully manifested. The practitioner fully integrated. The projection possible.],
  [*Secret Fire*],       [The vital force present within the mineral itself, operating autonomously once the correct conditions have been established. Not external heat.],
  [*Spagyric*],          [From the Greek _spao_ (to separate) and _ageiro_ (to gather). The art of separating, purifying, and reuniting the three principles of a plant preparation.],
  [*Via Humida*],        ["The Wet Path" — approach to the mineral kingdom through successive dissolutions, evaporations, and cohobations at moderate temperatures.],
  [*Via Sicca*],         ["The Dry Path" — approach to the mineral kingdom through high-temperature fusion and calcination.],
  [*Vitrification*],     [The glazing of plant salt caused by calcination above 400°C. The salt melts and fuses, losing its capacity to absorb the essence. Fatal to the preparation.],
  [*Vase of Hermes*],    [The sealed vessel in which the matter is enclosed for long digestion. Once sealed it is not opened. The Hanged Man (Key XII).],
  [*World Spirit*],      [Spiritus Mundi — the universal animating force that pervades and sustains all of creation. The operative substance of all alchemical work.],
)
